        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 12:06AM MDT by NWS Riverton WY</headline>
        <description>At 1205 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Anchor Dam, which is 24 miles north of Pavillion, moving northeast at
25 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of southwestern Hot
Springs County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
